## Testing (Test-AutoDocGeneration.ps1)

Automated test wrapper that validates single-file generation:

```powershell
# Test all file types from start
.\Test-AutoDocGeneration.ps1 -StartFromIndex 0

# Resume from specific index (uses QuickRun for index > 0)
.\Test-AutoDocGeneration.ps1 -StartFromIndex 2
```

**Test Workflow:**
1. Calls `AutoDocBatchRunner.ps1 -Regenerate single -SingleFile <path>`
2. Validates generated HTML (CSS, icon, image refs)
3. Opens HTML in Edge browser
4. Extracts Mermaid content to `.extracted.mmd` files
5. Converts MMD to SVG using `mmdc` (if available)
6. Opens SVG in browser for visual verification
7. Auto-continues to next file (non-interactive)

**Test Files:**
| Index | Type | File |
|-------|------|------|
| 0 | CBL | AABELMA.CBL |
| 1 | REX | WKMONIT.REX |
| 2 | BAT | Catalog-All-Db2-Azure-Databases-Using-Kerberos-For-Db2Client.bat |
| 3 | PS1 | Db2-CreateInitialDatabases.ps1 |
| 4 | SQL | DBM.FAKTHIST99B (table name, not file) |
| 5 | CSHARP | ServerMonitor.sln |

**Output Files:**
- `Test-AutoDocGeneration.log` - Execution log
- `Test-AutoDocGeneration.results.json` - Structured results
- `$env:OptPath\data\AutoDoc\extracted\` - MMD/SVG files

