## File Paths in Code

### AutodocFunctions.psm1 Path Patterns

```powershell
# Templates folder
$templatePath = Join-Path $PSScriptRoot "..\..\DevTools\LegacyCodeTools\AutoDoc\_templates"

# CSS folder
$cssFolder = Join-Path $sharedFolder "_css"
$sharedCssPath = Join-Path $cssFolder "autodoc-shared.css"

# Image paths (relative in output)
$Template.Replace("[iconurl]", "./_images/dedge.ico")
$Template.Replace("[imageurl]", "./_images/dedge.svg")

# JS paths (relative in output, with cache bust)
$Template.Replace("[controlsscripturl]", "./_js/autodoc-diagram-controls.js?v=$cacheBust")
$Template.Replace("[mermaidconfigurl]", "./_js/autodoc-mermaid-config.js?v=$cacheBust")
```

### AutoDocBatchRunner.ps1 Copy Logic

```powershell
# Source folders (use underscore prefix)
$jsSourceFolder = Join-Path $PSScriptRoot "_js"
$cssSourceFolder = Join-Path $PSScriptRoot "_css"
$imagesSourceFolder = Join-Path $PSScriptRoot "_images"
$templatesSourceFolder = Join-Path $PSScriptRoot "_templates"

# Target folders (same underscore prefix)
$targetJsFolder = Join-Path $webFolderRoot "_js"
$targetCssFolder = Join-Path $webFolderRoot "_css"
$targetImagesFolder = Join-Path $webFolderRoot "_images"
```

