## Parser Functions (AutodocFunctions.psm1)

Main parser entry points:

| Function | Purpose | Input |
|----------|---------|-------|
| `Start-CblParse` | Parse COBOL source files | `.cbl` file path |
| `Start-RexParse` | Parse Object REXX scripts | `.rex` file path |
| `Start-Ps1Parse` | Parse PowerShell scripts | `.ps1` file path |
| `Start-BatParse` | Parse Windows batch files | `.bat` file path |
| `Start-SqlParse` | Parse SQL table definitions | Table name (SCHEMA.TABLE) |
| `Start-CSharpParse` | Parse C# solution/project | `.sln` or `.csproj` path |
| `Start-CSharpEcosystemParse` | Parse multi-project C# ecosystem | Root folder path |

**Common Parameters:**
- `-SourceFile` / `-SourceFolder` - Input path
- `-OutputFolder` - Where to write HTML
- `-Show` - Open in browser after generation
- `-CleanUp` - Remove temp files
- `-ClientSideRender` - Use Mermaid.js in browser
- `-SaveMmdFiles` - Keep .mmd source files

---

## IIS Local Deployment (_deployLocalIIS.ps1)

Deploy AutoDoc as IIS virtual application:

```powershell
# Deploy
.\_deployLocalIIS.ps1 -Action Deploy

# Check status
.\_deployLocalIIS.ps1 -Action Status

# Teardown
.\_deployLocalIIS.ps1 -Action Teardown

# Full redeploy with cleaning
.\_deployLocalIIS.ps1 -Action Redeploy -CleanGeneratedFiles
```

**After deployment:** `http://localhost/AutoDoc/`

---

## Handler Functions (AutoDocBatchRunner.ps1)

| Function | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| `HandleCblFiles` | Process all COBOL files |
| `HandleScriptFiles` | Process REX, BAT, PS1 files |
| `HandleSqlTables` | Process SQL tables from DB2 |
| `HandleCSharpProjects` | Process C# solutions |
| `HandleCobdokExport` | Export metadata from cobdok database |
| `CreateJsonFileCbl` | Generate CblParseResult.json |
| `CreateJsonFileScript` | Generate ScriptParseResult.json |
| `CreateJsonFileSql` | Generate SqlParseResult.json |
| `CreateJsonFileCSharp` | Generate CSharpParseResult.json |

